Crew":4,"sleeps":8,"basePort":{"uri":"a::place::738f24c0-dada-11ed-befa-d7914edd5e3a","name":"Marina Kastela","coordinates":{"latitude":43.54601254691691,"longitude":16.40283517494042},"country":"Croatia"},"cruisingCapacity":8,"builtYear":2023,"architect":"","interiorDesigner":"","topSpeed":20,"cruiseSpeed":10,"fuelCapacity":1200,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Master Cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"Double Cabin","value":"3"}],"cabins":4,"bathrooms":4,"length":21.3,"beam":11.35,"draft":2.3,"hullType":"Catamaran","superStructure":[],"engines":"2 x 625 KW (850hp) MAN i6-850","amenities":[{"label":"Bow thruster"},{"label":"Flybridge"},{"label":"Teak deck"},{"label":"Sprayhood"},{"label":"Bimini top"},{"label":"Awning"},{"label":"Cockpit Cushions"},{"label":"Bathing platform & ladders","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Aft shower"},{"label":"Cooker with oven"},{"label":"Refrigerator","quantity":"3"},{"label":"Wine cooler"},{"label":"Cockpit Refrigerator & Icemaker"},{"label":"Microwave Oven / Grill"},{"label":"Icemaker"},{"label":"Dishwasher"},{"label":"Washing Machine/Dryer"},{"label":"Watermaker"},{"label":"Water heater"},{"label":"Holding tanks"},{"label":"Battery charger"},{"label":"USB plugs"},{"label":"Generators"},{"label":"Inverter"},{"label":"Navigational instruments"},{"label":"External Cameras"},{"label":"Additional wireless VHF"},{"label":"Radar / AIS"},{"label":"Air Conditioning"},{"label":"Heating system"},{"label":"Sunbathing Area"}],"toys":[{"label":"Seabob","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Onboard Jet ski"},{"label":"Water skies for adults and children"},{"label":"Wakeboard, monoski & kneeboard"},{"label":"Water tube and Towable ring"},{"label":"SUP (stand-up paddles)","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Kayak with two seats"},{"label":"Snorkeling Gear: Masks & flippers"},{"label":"Beach games, chargers and floating mats"},{"label":"Treadmill on Flybridge"},{"label":"Fishing gear"}],"entertainment":["Heos by Denon Surround 5.1","Bluetooth enabled","Digital Cloud (DLNA for movies and music)","Aux audio port","Audio remote control","Speakers in Saloon & Cockpit, Flybridge, Bownet","TV set & Satellite","DVD / Blu-ray player","Internet Wi-Fi"],"tenders":["Rib Turbojet Williams 100 hp"]},"crew":[{"name":"BORIS VRHOVAC","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::8193426698::vessel::77940a05-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::e5abd3e0-e498-11ef-a24e-a7ee3b2df502/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian / Born 1979 / ENGLISH, CROATIAN\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nMCA/RYA Off shore Yacht Master 500GT, D2 Basic Safety (SWTCW) Certificate.\n\nCaptain Boris Vrhovac, born 1979 in Zagreb, Croatia, has been sailing since he was a boy, first with his parents, and then as he grew older he continued to sail with his friends.\nAfter his first job as a skipper when he was 19, he knew that this was exactly what he wanted to do in life. Boris completed his MCA/RYA Yacht Master Offshore based in the Solent, UK and holds D2 Basic Safety (STCW) Certificate.\nHe is a fluent English speaker and can get by in Italian, French and German. Bringing extensive experience from our Lagoon 560, Lagoon 620, and Sunreef 60, he has served as Amber One’s captain from the very beginning.\nBoris has a calm nature which makes him pleasant to be around and enables him to keep a cool head in handling any situation that can occur. Boris is a wine enthusiast and a foodie."},{"name":"DRAGAN DRAGOJLOVIĆ GAGA","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::8193426698::vessel::77940a05-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::163cfe80-e499-11ef-882f-51ab7b385895/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian / Born 1985 / ENGLISH, ITALIAN, CROATIAN\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nGraduate diploma in Culinary Arts, Boat Leader Category B, D2 Basic Safety (STCW)\n\nChef and food stylist, Dragan Dragojlovic made the Croatian luxury yachting world richer for an outstanding professional, that completes every assignment in response to his guests most demanding needs. His vision of food, what food is supposed to be and the appearance of each plate is a story in itself. His approach to cooking, creativity and knowledge is what makes the difference. When we talk about food, we can openly state chef Dragan is simply creative with a touch of genius. Chef also holds the Basic captain license & D2 Basic Safety (STCW) Certificate. Dragan’s yacht experience includes working aboard Lagoon 620 and Sunreef 60. Dragan was a chef and sous chef in different restaurants, food stylist, crew Chef & Assistant Quartermaster at Celebrity MasterChef TV show."},{"name":"MARIJA JURETIĆ","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::77940a05-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::16b6eb40-da9a-11ef-aa5d-eb0a872d8649/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian / Born 1991 / ENGLISH, GERMAN, SPANISH\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nTrained Stewardess, Silver service, Boat skipper category A, D2 Basic, Safety (STCW)\n\nA Stewardess Marija Juretic was born in 1991 in Split, Croatia where she graduated from University of Economics in Split. She is a reliable person with a positive and friendly attitude, providing excellent customer service to clients while ensuring their comfort and safety throughout the cruise. She has extensive experience in hospitality and working in teams. After her graduation, she decided to experience something new and different. Marija joined captain Boris Vrhovac on Lagoon 620 in season 2018, where she fell in love with yachting. In 2019 she decided to apply and pursue the course in hospitality as the part of the UK butler education & silver service. Marija regularly practices CrossFit and has an interest in nutrition, fitness and holistic lifestyles. She loves training, running, cycling, walking in nature and animals."},{"name":"TIN DRUŽIĆ","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::8193426698::vessel::77940a05-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::645a8430-df0c-11ef-a6ef-efb12b3ddf65/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian/Born in 1993/ CROATIAN, ENGLISH\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nYachtmaster up to 1000GT), D2 Basic, Safety (STCW)\n\nTin’s passion for the sea began in early childhood and naturally developed into a lifelong career. Growing up around boats, he gained practical maritime knowledge from a young age, building strong seamanship skills that later shaped his professional path. \nAlthough he graduated with a degree in Physical Education, Tin chose to follow his nautical calling and dedicate himself fully to yachting. His academic background in sports and physical training gives him excellent discipline, endurance, and a strong sense of teamwork\n— qualities that are invaluable onboard. Tin joined AMBER ONE in 2024, bringing dynamic energy and enthusiasm to the crew. With a passion for sports and cross-fit, he actively supports and assists guests with water sports activities, ensuring both safety and enjoyment\nat all times. Tin is always attentive, proactive, and ready to help."}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":4900000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":4900000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"EUR","price":7500000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":7500000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"Until April 25, 2026","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2025-11-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-04-25T23:59:59.999Z"}],"pricing":{"currency":"EUR","charterFee":4900000,"inputAmountTaxed":"EXCLUSIVE","note":"","unit":"WEEK","lineItems":[{"item":"Charter Fee","quantity":1,"unitPrice":4900000,"amount":4900000,"taxRate":{"label":"VAT","value":0.13}},{"item":"APA","conditions":"","quantity":0.3,"unitPrice":4900000,"amount":1470000}],"total":7007000,"subTotal":6370000,"totalTax":637000},"inclusionZones":[{"label":"Croatia","type":"Sovereign country","category":["Europe","Southern Europe","Croatia"],"coordinates":[16.818610292079534,44.700266827856225],"bbox":[13.517187500000006,42.432910156249996,19.400976562500006,46.534619140625]}],"exclusionZo